      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FARROH JOE (5) is yet to win but has started his career in promising fashion with four placings from five runs. Recorded yet another strong performance last time when he battled on bravely to finish second over 2190m at Maryborough, adding to his reputation as a genuine performer. Has the ability to find the winners' list. HOLD ON FOREVER (1) drew a wide gate last start and was never a genuine threat, beaten 12 metres into sixth at Geelong over 2100m. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this better draw. Meets a comparable field and he can figure in the finish. FIFTY SEVEN CHEVY (2) is in the mix at his first run since finishing runner-up over 1690m at Kilmore 15 months ago. ROBUST SALLY (7) has place prospects if she can recapture the form from two starts back that saw her finish third over 2080m at this track.",
